<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05019b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05019b">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05019b"> 19(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hissed for <font color="green">[a pot]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The show should also include the hornets that Jehovah promised to send before the Jews to drive out the Hivite, the Canaanite, and the Hittite from the promised land, and the flies that he <mark>&ldquo;hissed for&rdquo;</mark> from the uttermost part of the rivers of Egypt. According to Bruce, the traveller, this must mean the <i>zimb</i>, which is not an ordinary fly, but a big, strong insect that bores through the skin of man and beast, and makes wounds even on the backs of rhinoceroses and elephants. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Bible Animals] 156</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
